		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/044409.html">Starting EQ takes too long...</a></B><P>

Tremelo wrote:
"I have a cable modem and my datarate.txt is set to 14."<P>

<B>Actually, we don't recommend that you set it higher than 9. 7 is probably better. It seems that setting it too high can cause trouble as much as setting it too low.</B><P>

"1. on the license agreement, make the "I accept" button the default."<P>

<B>Can't do that. From what I understand (and not by any official legal information source), it needs to be set this way so that you are consciously choosing to accept the agreement.</B><P>

"2. on the connect screen, you have 2 field: username and password. Make the username field accept the username, server and character you want to log into. ie: username/server/character.
If the server is invalid (or down) it drops you to the Server select screen. If the character name is invalid, it drops you to the character select screen."<P>

<B>Well, this might be possible. But it certainly takes me longer to type in my username/server/character than it does to click the appropriate buttons. I don't think this would decrease the load time.<P>

Personally, since I've moved to San Diego I can't get connected at any speed faster than 28.8. It _seems_ to me that it takes longer to load the game. But I'm well aware that this could only be an appearance (since I'm so miffed about my cruddy connection speed). I can recommend more than 64 megs of RAM if you want to increase your in-game performance. I went from 64 to 128 (actually, 192), and things seem a lot smoother for me. But your mileage may vary…<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/042820-4.html">Shaman Talk… (Part Two) By Absor</a></B><P>

Rathjar wrote: "so whats the deal?"<P>

<B>The deal is: we just got back from vacation. Nothing has really been 'done' about any of this yet, since we tried very hard not to think about EverQuest while we were visiting family and all that other holiday stuff.<P>

But we haven't forgotten anything.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/044595.html">Verant, PLEASE turn my account back on!</a></B><P>

If anyone in authority reads this, please email me<P>

<B>Is the email address attached to your account information accurate? That might be why you haven't received an e-mail.<P>

Alan</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
