				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				One other thing that I noticed, for game speed once you get in, is to MINIMIZE the time you spend in the character select screen.  If you spend more than about a minute there, your in-game speed will crawl, if you log out (Back to desktop) and then back in, without a long pause at char select, apparent speed seems to be much better.<BR>
<BR>
Ram does seem to help, as has been mentioned before, and the Video card ram has very little to add at this point.  (My current system:  NT Pro, Dual 733 Pent III, 256 Meg Rhambus Ram, Voodoo 5 graphics card with 64 Meg of memory, over a cable modem)
